# Figma Wireframe Layout Idea

## Frame

- Device: Desktop 1440 x 3000
- Grid: 12 columns
- Margin: 80 px
- Gutter: 20 px

## Sections

### Header / Navbar

- Purpose: Primary navigation and quick brand recognition.
- Height target: 72 px.
- Layout: Logo on the left, links on the right.
- Content: Home, About, Facts, Gallery.
- Notes: Dark background with optional subtle blur.

### Hero

- Purpose: Introduce Earth with visual impact and clear call-to-action.
- Height target: ~700 px.
- Layout: Two columns (left content, right featured image card).
- Content: H1, subtitle, two action buttons, large rounded image.
- Notes: Keep the image dominant but balanced with text.

### About

- Purpose: Provide context and core Earth information.
- Height target: ~650 px.
- Layout: Two columns (left image, right text).
- Content: Heading, paragraph, bullet list.
- Notes: Match spacing rhythm used in hero section.

### Facts

- Purpose: Quick scan section for key data points.
- Height target: ~600 px.
- Layout: Title and intro above a 3-column card grid.
- Content: Six fact cards, three per row on desktop.
- Notes: Card style uses subtle panel, border, and 18 px radius.

### Gallery

- Purpose: Visual storytelling through curated Earth imagery.
- Height target: ~650 px.
- Layout: Title and intro above a 3x2 image grid.
- Content: Six image tiles, consistent dimensions.
- Notes: Use 220 px image height and 18 px border radius.

### Footer

- Purpose: Attribution and source references.
- Height target: ~120 px.
- Layout: Two aligned text blocks (left/right).
- Content: "Created by..." and "Sources...".
- Notes: Stack content vertically on mobile.

## Components

- Button
- Fact Card
- Gallery Image Tile

## Responsive Rules

- Desktop: 12-column grid with two-column hero and about sections.
- Mobile (<= 768 px): Stack two-column sections into one column.
- Mobile (<= 768 px): Collapse facts and gallery grids to one column.
- Mobile (<= 768 px): Reduce spacing and heading scale.

